properties.Name: Great Sand Dunes National Park
properties.description: This is "ground zero" for UFO reports in the Valley. Visit Patti Vittoria at the Great Sand Dunes Oasis. Just outside the park entrance RV hookups, tent sites, restaurant, gas. Tell her Chris said hi!

properties.Name: Zapata Falls State Park
properties.description: South of the GSD Park about 8 miles is Zapata Falls SP. Go up the Zig Zag Radio Tower Road. At the Top. Sit at Dusk and look E toward the hillside w/ the burnt trees 1/4 mile away. This is where the sprite lights are. Hike the trail up to the Falls and sit in the grotto. This is where Steven Greer was allegedly contacted.

properties.Name: Blanca Peak
properties.description: Sacred Mtn of the East to the Dine', this is also ground zero for hundreds of UAP/AAO/UFO reports. Any spot on the west side is prime UFO watching site. Balls of light are often seen bouncing around on the mtn. Small craft have been seen going in and out of the surrounding terrain for decades.

properties.Name: Dollar Lake—San Luis Lakes State Park
properties.description: Possible "sipapu" or place of emergence for the Dine/Tewa/Pueblo Indians. Camping, RV, fishing. Great Skywatching location to watch Dunes and Blanca.

properties.Name: Witch Rock
properties.description: Site of alleged occult activity, orbs, strange creature sightings, etc

properties.Name: Mouth of Costilla Canyon
properties.description: Before you get to Amalia, NM 5 or 6 miles up the road from Costilla. This is the general area where a bigfoot was spotted in 2005. Rumors of a "portal" opening here along w/ ET entity sightings and craft sightings

properties.Name: Punche Valley
properties.description: Possible base location somewhere in this area. Watch out for the locals. Strange encounters w/ military, craft sightings, orbs, black choppers, etc. ***INVESTIGATE AT YOUR OWN RISK***

properties.Name: San Antonio Mtn
properties.description: Tewa say this is where Maasaaw lives (God of Death) when he comes out he's a bigfoot. Strange lava tubes and columns of air. Six BF sightings in '94 on northside between Mtn and Fox Creek. Craft, orb sightings

properties.Name: Fox Creek
properties.description: Bigfoot sightings

properties.Name: Kings Mine
properties.description: Oldest mine in NoAmerica 10K yrs old

properties.Name: Chama Canyon
properties.description: Hardest hit mutilation local in America--50-60 cases in 2 years! Very Hispano, respect the locals and tread carefully in Costilla County.

properties.Name: Ute Mtn
properties.description: Between Ute Mtn & Rio Grande Gorge. Strange military activity, choppers, low flying planes etc. ***INVESTIGATE AT YOUR OWN RISK***

properties.Name: Greenie Mtn
properties.description: Site of the NORAD Event Jan '94. Lots of UFO sightings, weird low flying B-52s, orbs, steel doors in ground, possible base location?

properties.Name: Alamosa
properties.description: Great central location to stay and plan day trips. Largest town in the valley—all the amenities. I recommend the Rio Grande Inn & Water Park near the corner of Highways 17 & 160, Oscars Mexican restaurant on Main St (GREAT chili rellanos), the San Luis Valley Brewing Co. and the Milagros Coffee Shop both also on Main St.

properties.Name: Middle Creek Hill
properties.description: Site of dozens of reports of small craft flying into the mountain 1/2 the way up. Look above the gravel pit on east side of the road.

properties.Name: Maxiville Area
properties.description: Location of mutes, orbs, black choppers and triangles, and other sightings. Anywhere along the Rio Grande from here to Del Norte is a good region to explore.

properties.Name: Dry Lakes Area
properties.description: History of Craft/Light sightings—especially in the late 1960s. Weird magnetic anomaly area, compasses spin etc

properties.Name: South of Del Norte
properties.description: From the "D" Mtn south—major UFO sightings in this area through the mid 1990s

properties.Name: Mineral Hot Springs/Joyful Journey
properties.description: Lithium Water—best springs I've ever experienced! Careful driving after soaking. Camping, Teepees, steam room, incredible views, bliss.

properties.Name: Crestone/Baca Grande
properties.description: One of USA's most unique towns. Gas, stores, shops, restaurants, motels, B&Bs, Inns, golf, camping, RV park. Monasteries, churches, temples, dojos, ashrams, stupas, retreat centers, etc, Drive out into the Baca Grande and explore the creeks. There are countless great skywatching spots overlooking one of America's most active UFO hot spots!.

properties.Name: Conejos Canyon
properties.description: Site of over a dozen Bigfoot sightings since the 1990s during the warmer months.

properties.Name: Penitente Canyon
properties.description: Stories of occult group, witches and brujo/bruja activity

properties.Name: Bishops Rock
properties.description: Anomaly zone w/ nearby 'gravity hill.' Reports of elementals, unintentional teleportation, unusual light phenomenon. Recommended!

properties.Name: Wheeler Geologic Area
properties.description: Amazing cubinsis-shaped rock formations, Native Sacred Site, UFO reports & also to the west and south

properties.Name: Unexplained blow down area
properties.description: Large acre-sized swath of trees flattened along the Continental Divide.

properties.Name: Independence Goldmine
properties.description: Extensive gold mine w/ miles upon miles of tunnels—an alleged "underworld" entrance. Also where miners in the 1880s, in the nearby mining camp, interacted with a bigfoot they nicknamed 'Boji.'

properties.Name: Villa Grove Turquoise Mine
properties.description: Possibly the oldest mine in North America, this site has been mined by humans for almost 10,000 years.

properties.Name: The Brownie Hills
properties.description: Site of numerous UFO reports in the mid-to-late 1960s

properties.Name: Valley View Hot Springs
properties.description: Clothing optional hot springs, location of morphing object overflight, photographed by Michael MacLaughlin in 2007.

properties.Name: Joyful Journey Hot Springs Spa
properties.description: Site of the July 1992 large craft landing. Best hot springs I've ever soaked in! Lithium water, careful—best to bring a designated driver who doesn't soak!

properties.Name: Blue Lake
properties.description: Sacred Lake of the Tewa Indians. Permission needed to visit.

properties.Name: Rio Grande Gorge Bridge
properties.description: Famous bridge across the breathtaking Rio Grande Gorge

properties.Name: Portal Activity
properties.description: Large overhanging rock face on trail, about 1/4 mile from trailhead. Brilliant red orbs reported numerous times coming and going from rock face.

properties.Name: Shaman's Cave
properties.description: Cave in cliff face about 400' up. Extremely difficult climb and dangerous to visit, do so at own risk.

properties.Name: White quartz outcropping
properties.description: Large outcropping of pure quartz that can be seen from across the valley—perfect meditation and/or skywatching location

properties.Name: Summitville Gold Mine
properties.description: Site of repeated alleged UFO craft and being visits with the mine site caretaker during the winter months in the mid 1960s.

properties.Name: NEW! Cerra de la Olla Encounter
properties.description: On 9-2-2019 two hunters encounter a huge, landed ship on top of Cerra de la Olla. The day before, one of the hunters witnessed two tall beings w/ large heads that appeared to be non-human.

properties.Name: NEW! Trickle Mountain
properties.description: NEW! Bigfoot trackway discovered by father and son while hunting in October 2019. Reported to the Fish & Wildlife Game Warden INVESTIGATION-IN-PROGRESS

properties.Name: NEW! Suspected Bigfoot scream
properties.description: Father and son hear an impossibly-loud scream September 2010
